{EAST has 14 points and opens her 4-card \C suit.

WEST must respond, and with two 4-card Majors bids them "up-the-line", saying 1\H.

EAST now shows his 4-card \S suit, and WEST again must bid. Since WEST is pretty weak he just 
raises to 2\S, which EAST happily passes.}

